                        impressions, one oblierated, another legible, both intaglio-carved in three
                        nasta‘līq script lines read from bottom upwards, single-ruled:</summary>
                     <seal type="stamp" subtype="circle">
                        <p>Obliterated seal, possibly with the name <persName>‘Ārif</persName>.<lb/>
                           <dimensions type="seal" unit="mm">
                              <dim type="diameter">~32</dim>
                           </dimensions></p>
                     </seal>
                     <seal type="stamp" subtype="circle">
                        <p>A legible seal impression of former owner <persName role="fmo seal ins"
                              >Mīr Taqī ‘Alī Fidvī</persName>, during the reign of Mughal Emperor
                              <persName role="asn" key="person_48143049"
                              ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/48143049">Muḥammad Farrukh Siyar (b. 1687 r.
                              1713–1719)</persName>, below his notation describing his purchase of
                           the volume:<lb/>
                           <q xml:lang="fa" cert="medium">میر تقی علی فدوی بادشاه غازی محمد فرخ سیر
                              عالمگیر ثانی</q><lb/>
                           <lb/>
                           <dimensions type="seal" unit="mm">
                              <dim type="diameter">~36</dim>
                           </dimensions> diam.</p>
                     </seal>
                  </sealDesc>
